abstract: Transparency about salaries can make workplaces more equitable, especially for women and people of color. Why are so few Americans willing to open up?

abstract: The candidates to lead Angela Merkel’s conservative party reflect a pivot away from the chancellor’s centrist legacy. All are men from the conservative west.
snippet: The candidates to lead Angela Merkel’s conservative party reflect a pivot away from the chancellor’s centrist legacy. All are men from the conservative west.
lead_paragraph: BERLIN — A week after Angela Merkel’s chosen successor threw her conservative party into disarray by announcing she would step down, the candidates who have emerged seem to represent the antithesis of the centrist chancellor from Germany’s east.

abstract: The Washington publication The Hill issued a lengthy report on Wednesday finding fault with several articles by journalist John Solomon that it published last year and were used as discredited narratives by President Donald Trump and many of his supporters in their fight against impeachment.

lead_paragraph: NEW YORK — The Washington publication The Hill issued a lengthy report on Wednesday finding fault with several articles by journalist John Solomon that it published last year and were used as discredited narratives by President Donald Trump and many of his supporters in their fight against impeachment.
headline_main: The Hill Criticizes, but Does Not Recant, Solomon Articles
headline_print_headline: The Hill Criticizes, but Does Not Recant, Solomon Articles

abstract: His moderate opposition is divided, and he seems in position to secure a large delegate lead on Super Tuesday.
snippet: His moderate opposition is divided, and he seems in position to secure a large delegate lead on Super Tuesday.
lead_paragraph: Senator Bernie Sanders has improved his standing in national polls since his victory in the New Hampshire primary, raising the possibility that he could amass a commanding or even insurmountable delegate lead on Super Tuesday in two weeks.
